I see the point of having formatted_operands, i.e. if the operand is somehow interpreted.
But in my opinion this makes only things worse... My plan would be to drop it completely.
@androguard/external-contributors what do you think? Are there any reason why we should keep it?

Currently, the get_intent_filters method in apk.py returns list type.
So we don't know each attribute name.

\<action\> and \<category\> tag only has 'name' atrribute but \<data\> tag has so many attributes(scheme, host, mimetype).

I suggest how about change the return format of get_intent_filter like this.
```sh
>> before
{'action':['com.samsung.android.support.REMOTE_ACTION']}>
>> after
{'action': [{'name': 'com.samsung.android.support.REMOTE_ACTION'}]}
```

```py
def get_intent_filters(self, itemtype, name):
        attributes = {"action": ["name"], "category": ["name"], "data": ["scheme", "host", "port", "path", "pathPattern", "pathPrefix", "mimeType"]}
        d = {}
        for element in attributes.keys():
            d[element] = []

        for i in self.xml:
            # TODO: this can probably be solved using a single xpath
            for item in self.xml[i].findall(".//" + itemtype):
                if self._format_value(item.get(self._ns("name"))) == name:
                    for sitem in item.findall(".//intent-filter"):
                        for element in d.keys():
                            for ssitem in sitem.findall(element):
                                result = {}
                                for attribute in attributes[element]:
                                    value = ssitem.get(self._ns(attribute))
                                    if value is None:
                                        continue
                                    result[attribute] = value

                                if result:
                                    d[element].append(result)

        for element in list(d.keys()):
            if not d[element]:
                del d[element]

        return d
```

